Description: Cell lines are key experimental models to understand protein interactions and signaling pathways. With a large pool of such data coming from different cell lines of different origin -of normal and -pathological tissues- proper analysis requires segregating data pertaining to specific cell lines. The project envisaged brings together hierarchical trees of organs- mammalian cell lines and diseases in one platform. Certain specific terms from Cell Type (CL) ontology- Foundational Model of Anatomy (FMA) and DOID ontologies are mapped for searchability. Ontology is developed in both OBO and OWL.
Authors: Name: BioPortal project on behalf of ontology owner.; Email:support@bioontology.org
